From e87c55919a33b831ef097a0f1ee45cb69886ddfe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lukas Schwerdtfeger <lukas.schwerdtfeger@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 17:38:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix stale returnRef index by replacing hoisted ALLOCAs with
 tombstones

hoistAllocaOperations() previously erased ALLOCA ops from blocks,
invalidating the operationIndex stored in returnRefs. Now it replaces
them with ALLOCA_TOMBSTONE ops that preserve vector indices. Tombstones
are skipped in isLocalValueRef, getOrBuildDefinitions, and IR lowering,
then stripped alongside ASSIGN ops in removeAssignOperations.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
